[src:chaos-engineering-tools/chaos-engineering-the-history-principles-and-practice] Our blog covers use cases and practices using Chaos Engineering, such as preparing for cloud migrations and running GameDays.
[src:chaos-engineering-tools/chaos-engineering-the-history-principles-and-practice] Pavlos Ratis has created a GitHub repo called “Awesome Chaos Engineering,” which is a curated list of Chaos Engineering resources.
[src:chaos-engineering-tools/chaos-engineering-the-history-principles-and-practice] You can find Books, Tools, Papers, Blogs, Newsletters, Conferences, MeetUps, Forums and engineers to follow on Twitter.
