[src:chaos-engineering-tools/chaos-engineering-the-history-principles-and-practice] As web systems have grown much more complex with the rise of distributed systems and microservices, system failures have become difficult to predict.
[src:chaos-engineering-tools/chaos-engineering-the-history-principles-and-practice] So in order to prevent failures from happening, we all need to be proactive in our efforts to learn from failure.
[src:chaos-engineering-tools/chaos-engineering-the-history-principles-and-practice] In this guide, we shared a brief history of Chaos Engineering and demonstrated how Chaos Engineering offers you new insights into your systems.
[src:chaos-engineering-tools/chaos-engineering-the-history-principles-and-practice] We look forward to hearing about your Chaos Engineering journey and encourage you to share your progress with the Chaos Engineering community.
